  <ui-tests>
    <test name="LegalWorkspace renders identically (Risk R-4 verification)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi page → Workspace pane</step>
        <step>Switch through 3 layouts (matching the pre-change snapshot)</step>
        <step>For each layout: verify all sections render at the same positions as pre-change</step>
        <step>Verify scroll behavior, drag-and-drop, section close/expand interactions unchanged</step>
        <step>Verify console has no new warnings or errors</step>
        <step>Compare side-by-side (or pixel-diff) against pre-change snapshot</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>UI IDENTICAL to pre-change snapshot. ZERO observable behavioral diff (Risk R-4 mitigation).</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Default renderer registered (no host code change needed)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Confirm SpaarkeAi consumer code was NOT modified by this task (only @spaarke/* libs + LegalWorkspace)</step>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi page → Workspace pane</step>
        <step>Verify default rendering uses `LegalWorkspaceRenderer` (visually identical to before)</step>
        <step>Open dev console and inspect WorkspaceLayoutWidget mount — confirm renderer prop is either absent (defaulted) OR resolved to LegalWorkspaceRenderer from the registry</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>SpaarkeAi works without any code changes on its side; the default-renderer registration is the seam.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the new interface, When inspected, Then `WorkspaceRenderer` is defined in `@spaarke/ui-components` and exported from its public surface.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `LegalWorkspaceApp`, When inspected, Then it (or a thin sibling) implements `WorkspaceRenderer`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `WorkspaceLayoutWidget`, When inspected, Then it accepts an injected `renderer?` prop OR consults a renderer registry, with `LegalWorkspaceRenderer` as the registered default.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given Risk R-4 (zero behavioral diff today), When SpaarkeAi Workspace pane is exercised end-to-end, Then UI is IDENTICAL to the pre-change snapshot.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given SpaarkeAi as the existing consumer, When this task lands, Then SpaarkeAi source code is UNCHANGED — the seam is transparent.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `tsc --noEmit`, When run on `@spaarke/ui-components`, `@spaarke/ai-widgets`, `LegalWorkspace`, and `SpaarkeAi`, Then 0 type errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the W-1 doc, When inspected, Then it includes a cross-link to the new `WorkspaceRenderer` interface under "Two wrappers — Dashboard wrapper".</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The interface is a SEAM, not a feature. Do NOT add capabilities beyond what `LegalWorkspaceApp` already
    provides. The future-host extensibility framing (per spec) is forward-looking; today's behavior is
    the only behavior. Risk R-4 is real because seam introductions often subtly change mount timing, prop
    resolution, or context inheritance — the pre/post snapshot is the only reliable mitigation.

    If a renderer registry pattern is chosen (vs prop injection), keep it minimal: one registry, one
    default, one override point. Avoid plugin architectures, lifecycle hooks, or composition primitives.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>Load all files in &lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt; before starting. Apply FULL rigor protocol: rigor declaration at Step 0; pre-change snapshot is MANDATORY (Risk R-4 mitigation); Step 9.5 quality gates MANDATORY. ADR-012 + ADR-028 are LOAD-BEARING — verify interface remains context-agnostic and contains no token-snapshot expectations.</protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
